A captive portal is a web page that is often displayed before you can
access the Internet on public networks in airports, hotels, libraries,
and other places.

[[!img captive_portal.svg link="no" alt="Train station Wi-Fi. Click here for 60 minutes of free Wi-Fi" title="Example of a captive portal"]]

Tails cannot connect to the Tor network when the Internet connection is
initially blocked by a captive portal.
